b46de029f19\",\"slug\":\"clavicular-pregnancy-in-2026\",\"endDate\":\"2026-12-31T00:00:00Z\",\"startDate\":\"2026-04-20T22:41:29.998973Z\",\"description\":\"This market will resolve to \\\"Yes\\\" if Clavicular announces that he and a partner are expecting a baby through pregnancy between market creation and December 31, 2026, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to \\\"No\\\".\\n\\nOnly credible announcements will qualify. Pregnancy announcements that are not credible, for example jokes, will not suffice. This market will resolve based on the date of announcement, regardless of when the child is born.  \\n\\nThe resolution source will be statements from Clavicular or his representatives; however, a definitive consensus of credible media reporting may be considered.\",\"outcomes\":\"[\\\"Yes\\\", \\\"No\\\"]\",\"outcomePrices\":\"[\\\"1\\\", \\\"0\\\"]\",\"volume\":\"13934862.960998023\",\"active\":true,\"closed\":true,\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-20T22:28:48.129526Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:40:21.634529Z\",\"closedTime\":\"2026-05-01 00:33:40+00\",\"resolvedBy\":\"0x65070BE91477460D8A7AeEb94ef92fe056C2f2A7\",\"questionID\":\"0x24b6bade3cce1deaee8a6381420b7fb88b0f409b447747471b0245061d986280\",\"umaEndDate\":\"2026-05-01T00:33:40Z\",\"umaResolutionStatus\":\"resolved\",\"lastTradePrice\":0.999,\"bestBid\":0.998,\"bestAsk\":0.999,\"automaticallyResolved\":true,\"umaResolutionStatuses\":\"[\\\"proposed\\\", \\\"disputed\\\", \\\"proposed\\\", \\\"disputed\\\"]\"}],\"closedTime\":\"2026-05-01T00:33:40Z\",\"eventMetadata\":{\"context_description\":\"Trader consensus on Polymarket has locked in a 99.9% implied probability for Yes on Clavicular's pregnancy announcement in 2026, driven by Kick streamer Braden Peters' (aka Clavicular) repeated public vows to become a father by year-end, including his detailed fertility stack reveal and controversial pitch for a \\\"dating show\\\" to select a baby mama from 500 contestants. Recent viral backlash from his April livestream stunt--coupled with debunked rumors of an 18-year-old girlfriend's pregnancy after just 10 days, sparking emotional on-stream breakdowns--has amplified the narrative of imminent fatherhood. With $16 million in trading volume, the skin-in-the-game crowd sees his unfiltered influencer persona as a lock for some announcement before December 31. Realistic upsets remain slim but possible: a platform ban amid ongoing outrage, personal change of heart, or legal hurdles derailing his plans.\",\"context_requires_regen\":true,\"context_updated_at\":\"2026-05-01T00:31:22.155Z\"}}]\n\n[defendant] D-S1 Forbes fragment and limitations\nRetrieval/extraction notes: curl -L -A 'Mozilla/5.0' fetched the Forbes page. Grep over the HTML/Next.js payload for Clavicular/pregnant/market description terms returned the following relevant page text fragments and metadata.\n\nSource metadata:\n- Title: \"Polymarket's $16M Clavicular Bet Sparks Oracle Dispute\" / \"'Inmates Taking The Asylum'--Polymarket's $16M Clavicular Bet\"\n- Author: Boaz Sobrado\n- Publisher: Forbes Digital Assets\n- Published/modified: 2026-04-30T17:55:56-04:00\n- URL: https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2026/04/30/inmates-taking-the-asylum-polymarkets-16m-clavicular-bet/\n- Structured metadata description: \"Polymarket's $16M Clavicular pregnancy bet is testing UMA's oracle as top traders call the resolution layer 'a disinformation engine taken over by rogue traders.'\"\n- Page metadata says isAccessibleForFree: False.\n\nExtracted relevant fragments from article payload:\n- The disputed market, linked as \"Clavicular pregnancy in 2026?\", had done $16.46 million in lifetime volume on Polymarket, including roughly $4.5 million in the past 24 hours, and Yes shares traded at 97 cents.\n- Fragment: \"gotten a girl pregnant. The market's own rules state that 'pregnancy announcements that are not credible, for example jokes, will not suffice.' Other traders posting through the dispute, including @holy_mos