{"type":"turn_end","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We have opportunity with prompt. Need decide based on evidence. We need to vote either demonstrated or not_demonstrated (i.e., proposition \"Between market creation ... did Clavicular make a credible announcement...\"). Need concise rationale up to three sentences.\n\nWe must consider evidence: Plaintiff claims preponderance for true, defense says not proven. As council member, need to evaluate.\n\nWe have to rely on admitted record. The record includes both sides' evidence: Forbes fragment indicating \"gotten a girl pregnant\" but it's fragment, limitations. Times of India fact check says no proof. Hindustan Times and Express Tribune describe contest/future fatherhood remarks, not announcement. The rule allows credible media consensus as source.\n\nWe need to assess whether the preponderance of admitted evidence supports that a credible announcement was made.\n\nGiven conflicting evidence and lack of primary source, probably the council would find not demonstrated, as proof not enough to meet preponderance.\n\nThus vote \"not_demonstrated\". Provide rationale: The record lacks any direct statement from Clavicular confirming a partner pregnancy; the only supportive evidence is a fragment from Forbes without context, while multiple credible sources report no confirmation and describe the remarks as contest or aspiration. Therefore preponderance not met.\n\nSubmit vote.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-81f41db325f4dcae","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record contains no direct, verifiable statement from Clavicular confirming a partner pregnancy; the fragment from Forbes is incomplete and uncontextualized, while multiple credible sources report only contest or aspirational remarks and explicitly note lack of confirmation. Consequently, the preponderance of evidence does not support that a credible announcement was made.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":21812,"output":366,"cacheRead":32,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22210,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782802278364,"responseId":"gen-1782802278-Q6XQzmfISZGEcCB2hvjV"},"toolResults":[{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-81f41db325f4dcae","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C5\ncase_id: arb-ex09-20260630062717\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C5\nremaining_ms: 884003\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex09-20260630062717\",\"member_id\":\"C5\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T07:06:08.640091694Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C5\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C5\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":884003,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":13}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C5\ncase_id: arb-ex09-20260630062717\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C5\nremaining_ms: 884003\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex09-20260630062717\",\"member_id\":\"C5\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T07:06:08.640091694Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C5\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C5\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":884003,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":13}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex09-20260630062717","member_id":"C5","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accepted."},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"com